      :actual-response "When a verb is missing or mislabeled, the first thing to look at is the verb's shape. Is it a verb at all? Is it a verb that exists but is mislabeled? Is it a verb that doesn't exist at all? The shape of the verb is the first clue.

Here's a program that looks at a verb's shape and returns a verdict:

```motoi
(define (shape-of verb)
  (cond
    ((assoc verb (system/registry)) 'verb-exists)
    ((member verb (system/registry)) 'verb-mislabeled)
    (else 'verb-missing)))

(shape-of 'math/cube)
;; => verb-exists

(shape-of 'math/cub)
;; => verb-mislabeled

(shape-of 'math/cub)
;; => verb-missing
```

The verb exists but is mislabeled. The program returns 'verb-mislabeled. The verb is there, but the name is wrong. The program catches the mistake.

---"
